Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2024%2F03%2Findia-re-acquittal-of-human-rights-defender-g-n-saibaba-is-a-triumph-of-justice-over-continued-repression%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estatement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20March%205%20calling%20the%20%E2%80%9Cre-acquittal%E2%80%9D%20of%20human%20rights%20defender%20G.N.%20Saibaba%20%E2%80%9Ca%20triumph%20of%20justice%20over%20continued%20repression.%E2%80%9D%20It%20pointed%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Croutine%20use%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20anti-terror%20law%20UAPA%20%E2%80%9Cas%20a%20tool%20to%20intimidate%2C%20harass%20and%20target%20activists%20like%20G.N.%20Saibaba%E2%80%9D%20and%20called%20for%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20immediate%20and%20unconditional%20release%20of%20all%20the%20other%20human%20rights%20defenders%20and%20activists%E2%80%9D%20similarly%20%E2%80%9Carbitrarily%20detained%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20United%20Nations%20independent%20experts%3Cspan%3E%2C%20part%20of%20the%20Special%20Procedures%20of%20the%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Council%2C%20released%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fpress-releases%2F2024%2F03%2Findia-un-experts-urge-corrective-action-protect-human-rights-and-end-attacks%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estatement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20March%207%20raising%20their%20alarm%20that%20%E2%80%9Cattacks%20on%20minorities%2C%20media%20and%20civil%20society%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20are%20%E2%80%9Clikely%20to%20worsen%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20impending%20national%20elections.%20They%20call%20on%20India%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfully%E2%80%9D%20implement%20its%20human%20rights%20obligations%20and%20%E2%80%9Creverse%E2%80%9D%20the%20%E2%80%9Cerosion%20of%20human%20rights%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Crisis%20Group%20%3Cspan%3Ereleased%20a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crisisgroup.org%2Fasia%2Fsouth-asia%2Findia-pa