%20Parliament%20(Trinamool%20Congress)%2C%20and%20former%20journalist%2C%20Sagarika%20Ghose%20with%20Dr.%20Irfan%20Nooruddin%20of%20Georgetown%20University.%20In%20the%20context%20of%20Hindu%20nationalism%2C%20they%20discussed%20challenges%20facing%20Indian%20opposition%20leaders%2C%20including%20the%20use%20of%20anti-corruption%20tools%20to%20undermine%20Indian%20opposition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20the%20operationalization%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%202019%2C%20Amnesty%20International%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Ca%20blow%20to%20the%20Indian%20constitutional%20values%20of%20equality%20and%20religious%20non-discrimination%20and%20inconsistent%20and%20incompatible%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20international%20human%20rights%20obligations%E2%80%9D%20in%20a%20March%2014%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2024%2F03%2Findia-citizenship-amendment-act-is-a-blow-to-indian-constitutional-values-and-international-standards%2F%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20government%20has%20failed%20to%20%E2%80%9Clisten%20to%20a%20multitude%20of%20voices%20critical%20of%20the%20CAA%E2%80%9D.%20Amnesty%20notes%20that%20the%20CAA%20also%20expands%20the%20criteria%20for%20cancellation%20of%20the%20Overseas%20Citizen%20of%20India%20(OCI)%20registration%20as%20%E2%80%9Canother%20weapon%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctarget%20and%20punish%20dissenting%20voices%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0It%20demands%20the%20immediate%20repeal%20of%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fharpercollins.co.uk%2Fproducts%2Fthe-incarcerations-alpa-shah%3Fvariant%3D40286472962126%5C%22%3Ebook%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Alpa%20Shah%2C%20Professor%20of%20Anthropology%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20titled%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Incarcerations%3A%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20and%20the%20Search%20for%20Democracy%20in%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20alleges%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20interviews%20with%20cyber%20security%20analysts%2C%20that%20evidence%20used%20to%20incarcerate%2016%20people%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case%20was%20%E2%80%9Clikely%20to%20have%20been%20implanted%20remotely%20through%20a%20hacker-for-hire%20mercenary%20gang%20infrastructure%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20an%20Investigating%20Officer%20on%20the%20case%20worked%20with%20the%20hackers%20to%20plant%20evidence%20in%20the%20computers%20of%20at%20least%20three%20of%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpen%20Doors%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opendoors.org%2Fen-US%2Fpersecution%2Fcountries%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWorld%20Watch%20List%202024%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opendoors.org%2Fen-US%2Fpersecution%2Fcountries%2Findia%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eranked%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20India%20as%2011%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20their%20latest%20annual%20ranking%20of%20the%2050%20countries%20where%20Christians%20face%20the%20most%20severe%20persecution.%20Published%20last%20month%2C%20the%20report%20terms%20anti-Christian%20persecution%20in%20India%20as%20%E2%80%9Cextreme%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20highlights%20the%20targeting%20of%20Christians%20during%20the%20ethno-religious%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20as%20well%20as%20during%20mob%20attacks%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20both%20in%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20recently%20released%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2F2024%2F02%2F28%2Frepresentative-democracy-remains-a-popular-ideal-but-people-around-the-world-are-critical-of-how-its-working%2F%5C%22%3Efindings%20of%20its%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20popularity%20of%20representative%20democracy%20%E2%80%94%20and%20authoritarianism%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20around%20the%20world.%20Among%20its%20findings%20on%20India%20are%20that%20although%20people%20want%20democracy%20to%20be%20more%20representative%2C%2082%25%20said%20technocracy%20was%20at%20least%20somewhat%20good%2C%2072%25%20said%20military%20rule%20was%20at%20least%20somewhat%20good%20and%2067%25%20thought%20it%20was%20a%20good%20thing%20for%20a%20strong%20leader%20to%20be%20unconstrained%20by%20legislative%20or%20judicial%20interference.%20The%20share%20of%20the%20public%20that%20supports%20authoritarian%20systems%20was%20highest%20in%20India%20(85%25)%20and%20lowest%20in%20Sweden%20(8%25)%2C%20the%20median%20being%2031%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20V-Dem%20(Varieties%20of%20Democracy)%20Democracy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.v-dem.net%2Fpublications%2Fdemocracy-reports%2F%5C%22%3EReport%3C%2Fa%3E%202024%20observes%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cwave%20of%20autocratisation%20is%20observable%20globally%E2%80%9D.%20India%2C%20with%2018%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20%E2%80%9Caccounts%20for%20about%20half%20of%20the%20population%20living%20in%20autocratising%20countries.%E2%80%9D%20There%20has%20been%20sharp%20autocratisation%20in%20India%20from%202013%2C%20putting%20it%20at%20one%20of%20the%20top%20ten%20in%20recent%20times.%20It%20notes%20that%20India%20is%20no%20longer%20termed%20a%20democracy%2C%20but%20%E2%80%9Cdropped%20down%20to%20electoral%20autocracy%20in%202018%E2%80%9D%20and%20remains%20there%20at%20the%20end%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIndian%20diaspora%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternational%20Solidarity%20for%20Academic%20Freedom%20in%20India%20(InSAF%20India)%3Cspan%3E%20supported%20by%20several%20international%20diasporic%20groups%2C%20including%20from%20Canada%2C%20UK%2C%20Europe%2C%20and%20USA%2C%20organised%20an%20online%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2F2FYJL9nroTY%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eevent%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20celebrate%20the%20release%20of%20Prof.%20GN%20Saibaba%2C%20Prashant%20Rahi%2C%20Hem%20Mishra%2C%20Vijay%20Tirki%2C%20and%20Mahesh%20Tirki%2C%20on%20March%2010.%20InSAF%20India%20spoke%20about%20the%20need%20to%20honour%20them%20and%20their%20families%2C%20communities%2C%20and%20legal%20teams%2C%20and%20to%20commemorate%20the%20custodial%20death%20of%20co-accused%20Pandu%20Narote.%20The%20meeting%20was%20addressed%20by%20speakers%20from%20activism%2C%20law%2C%20literature%2C%20and%20art.%20Present%20at%20the%20event%2C%20Professor%20G.N.%20Saibaba%20emphasised%20the%20resilience%20of%20the%20imprisoned%20Adivasi%20and%20Dalit-Bahujan%20in%20prisons%20and%20their%20efforts%20to%20educate%20themselves%20against%20all%20odds%2C%20and%20on%20his%20work%20as%20a%20teacher%20with%20these%20co-prisoners.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711268142000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24134042%2FUntitled-design-6-2-e1711267863755.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Findia-globally-caa-manipur-and-indias-human-rights-crisis%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Here's%20a%20peek%20into%20exactly%20what%20from%20India%20made%20global%20news%20this%20fortnight.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Findia-globally-caa-manipur-and-indias-human-rights-crisis%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SSEL%20aims%20to%20make%20new%20plant%20operational%20in%20Jul-Sep%20qtr%2C%20says%20CMD%20Reddy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711268138000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-04%2F19%2Ffull%2F1681901132-3901.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fssel-aims-to-make-new-plant-operational-in-jul-sep-qtr-says-cmd-reddy-124032400196_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Reddy%20further%20said%20SSEL%20is%20also%20into%20transmission%20EPC%20projects%20and%20around%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20conductors'%20production%20will%20be%20consumed%20by%20the%20company's%20transmission%20business%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C