Ecited%3C%2Fa%3E%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20military%20occupation%20of%20Afghanistan%20in%20the%201980s%20and%20its%20long%20history%20of%20crackdowns%20on%20Muslim%20communities%20in%20Russia%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20North%20Caucasus.%20They%20have%20also%20cited%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20providing%20a%20lifeline%20to%20the%20brutal%20regime%20of%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20in%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20also%20likely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aymennaltamimi.com%2Fp%2Fislamic-state-claims-moscow-attacks%5C%22%3Eopportunity%20and%20personnel%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20led%20the%20group%20to%20select%20a%20soft%20target%20in%20Moscow%2C%20as%20much%20as%20anything%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIslamic%20State%20carried%20out%20multiple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fazelin%2Fstatus%2F1771276860237709441%5C%22%3Eattacks%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Russia%20from%202016%E2%80%9319%2C%20while%20several%20more%20plots%20were%20disrupted%20from%202021%E2%80%9323.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20ISIS-K%20militants%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feurasianet.org%2Firan-attack-signals-growing-central-asian-role-in-iskps-external-ops%5C%22%3Earrested%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20Europe%2C%20including%20in%20Russia%2C%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%20have%20been%20Russian%20nationals%20and%20people%20from%20Central%20Asia%20with%20links%20to%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20recent%20arrests%20occurred%20this%20month%20when%20Russian%20authorities%20claimed%20they%20prevented%20a%20planned%20attack%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-says-it-neutralized-isis-cell-plotting-attack-moscow-synagogue-2024-03-07%2F%5C%22%3Esynagogue%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20last%20month%2C%20a%20Russian%20national%20accused%20of%20having%20Islamic%20State%20links%20was%20arrested%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fpoland-detains-ru