ndia-reserve-chhattisgarh-jharkhand-wildlife-trust-of-india-udanti-sitanadi-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUdanti-Sitanadi%20tiger%20reserve%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewas%20used%20as%20a%20game%20reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBack%20then%2C%20anyone%20could%20shoot%20animals%20after%20paying%20a%20small%20fee.%20For%20instance%2C%20you%20could%20shoot%20a%20tiger%20paying%20Rs%2025%2C%20and%20wild%20buffalo%2C%20which%20is%20the%20state%20animal%2C%20with%20Rs%20100.%20This%20continued%20till%201972%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20the%20reason%20why%20we%20have%20such%20low%20numbers%20of%20tigers.%20Currently%2C%20we%20have%20just%20one%20tiger.%20This%20makes%20our%20tiger%20reserve%20different%20from%20the%20Kanha%2C%20Ranthambore%2C%20or%20Pilibhit%20tiger%20reserves.%20Because%20of%20the%20encroachment%2C%20we%20were%20not%20able%20to%20progress%20eco-tourism%20in%20the%20region.%20Just%20a%20year%20back%2C%20we%20did%20not%20even%20have%20any%20gypsy%20safaris%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20evicting%20encroachers%20to%20welcoming%20wildlife%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20field%20visits%20to%20the%20forest%2C%20Jain%20would%20often%20see%20large%20charred%20spots.%20%E2%80%9CI%20found%20out%20that%20giant%20100-year-old%20trees%20were%20burnt%20down%20to%20make%20huts%20and%20farmland.%20Immediately%2C%20I%20procured%20ISRO%20images%20from%202008%2C%202010%2C%20and%202012%2C%20and%20then%2C%20I%20conducted%20surveys%20using%20drones%20to%20assess%20the%20encroachment.%20After%20comparing%20both%20the%20images%2C%20we%20found%20out%20that%20the%20reserve%20was%20a%20dense%20forest%20until%202008.%20Now%2C%20it%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20an%20open%20forest%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202006%2C%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%20was%20enacted%20and%20it%20stated%20that%20any%20member%20or%20community%20that%20primarily%20resided